House Resolution 412
By: Representatives Stephens of the 164th and Petrea of the 166th
A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating the Savannah Country Day School clay target team for winning the 2024
2 Georgia State Clay Target Championship; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Savannah Country Day School clay target team has established and
4 maintained a proud tradition of excellence with equal emphases on character and discipline;
5 and
6 WHEREAS, the team brought special recognition to its school by winning the 2024 Georgia
7 State Clay Target Championship, with the varsity team competing against over 600 athletes
8 and 49 high school teams and achieving a dominant score of 1,383 out of 1,500, earning its
9 second state title; and
10 WHEREAS, the middle school team also delivered an exceptional performance at the
11 championship, defeating 12 other teams with a winning score of 525 out of 600, marking the
12 first state championship victory for the program at the middle school level; and
13 WHEREAS, since its inception in 2019, the Savannah Country Day School clay target team
14 has produced numerous individual and team accomplishments, including the 2022 individual
15 Georgia state champion, a two-time individual female Georgia state champion in 2021 and
