16 2023, an individual Georgia state championship runner-up in 2024, and two high school
17 national championship team runner-up finishes in 2023 and 2024; and
18 WHEREAS, the phenomenal performance of the team is a clear indication of the outstanding
19 athletic ability, dedication, hard work, and unity of purpose and spirit demonstrated by each
20 member of the team, as well as the astute direction of Head Coach Eric Haas; and
21 WHEREAS, the 2024 Savannah Country Day School clay target team was led by captains
22 Chase Buerger, Dan Bradley, and Miles Carson, who exemplified leadership and
23 sportsmanship in guiding their team to success; and
24 WHEREAS, as this magnificent team earned its well-deserved reputation for excellence by
25 performing with courage and precision over months of training and competition, it is
26 abundantly proper to call them champions.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body congratulate the Savannah Country Day School clay target team
29 for winning the 2024 Georgia State Clay Target Championship and extend best wishes for
30 their continued success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
33 Savannah Country Day School clay target team.
